    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so basically the water holds the temperature back until it's gone. one more thing though—the book mentioned that the reaction creates tons of different compounds that give food its \"complexity.\" can you give me some examples of these compounds? like, what are we actually producing that makes it taste so much better?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
